'''羅斯·威廉·烏布利希'''（{{lang-en|Ross William Ulbricht}}，{{bd|1984年|3月27日}}）是一名[[美国|美国]][[罪犯|罪犯]]，因於2011年創辦了[[暗網|暗網]]市場[[絲路_(購物網站)|絲路]]而知名于世。烏布利希於2013年被捕之前一直營運著“絲路”網站<ref name="ulbricht conviction">{{cite news|last1=Raymond|first1=Nate|title=Accused Silk Road operator convicted on U.S. drug charges|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2015/02/05/us-usa-bitcoin-trial-idUSKBN0L82H920150205|accessdate=2015-06-22|work=Reuters|date=2015-02-04|archive-date=2015-06-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150623080815/http://www.reuters.com/article/2015/02/05/us-usa-bitcoin-trial-idUSKBN0L82H920150205|dead-url=yes}}</ref>，該網站為確保匿名性，在設計上只允许透過[[Tor|Tor]]访问，並仅以[[比特幣|比特幣]]作為交易媒介<ref name="ars sunk" /><ref name="USA Today shutdown info" />。他的網名{{link-en|恐怖海盜羅伯茲|Dread Pirate Roberts}}取自《公主新娘》（The Princess Bride）及其改編電影中的同名角色。

2015年2月，烏布利希被美國當局控以[[洗錢|洗錢]]、[[骇客|電腦入侵]]、串謀[[販毒|販毒]]、串謀販運虛假身份证明文件等罪<ref>{{cite web|title=Jury Verdict|url=https://www.docketalarm.com/cases/New_York_Southern_District_Court/1--14-cr-00068/USA_v._Ulbricht/183/|publisher=Docket Alarm|accessdate=2016-09-27|archive-date=2016-10-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161001184453/https://www.docketalarm.com/cases/New_York_Southern_District_Court/1--14-cr-00068/USA_v._Ulbricht/183/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2015年5月，法院判處烏布利希双重[[無期徒刑|無期徒刑]]，40年內不得假釋。後來，他先後把案件上訴至[[美国联邦第二巡回上诉法院|美国联邦第二巡回上诉法院]]（2017）和[[美国最高法院|美国最高法院]]（2018），但兩度皆上訴失敗<ref>{{cite web|title=Silk Road founder loses his appeal, will serve a life sentence for online crimes|url=https://techcrunch.com/2017/05/31/ross-ulbricht-silk-road-appeal-denied/|publisher=Techcrunch.com|accessdate=2017-06-01|archive-date=2017-05-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170531225626/https://techcrunch.com/2017/05/31/ross-ulbricht-silk-road-appeal-denied/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Certiorari Denied |url=https://www.supremecourt.gov/orders/courtorders/062818zr_k425.pdf |publisher=Supreme Court of the United States |page=5 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20180629151235/https://www.supremecourt.gov/orders/courtorders/062818zr_k425.pdf |archive-date=2018-06-29 |access-date=2018-06-29 |deadurl=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Judgment in a Criminal Case (Sentencing)|url=https://www.docketalarm.com/cases/New_York_Southern_District_Court/1--14-cr-00068/USA_v._Ulbricht/269/|publisher=Docket Alarm|accessdate=2016-09-27|archive-date=2016-10-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161001192356/https://www.docketalarm.com/cases/New_York_Southern_District_Court/1--14-cr-00068/USA_v._Ulbricht/269/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。他現於{{link-en|亞利桑那州圖森監獄|United States Penitentiary, Tucson}}服刑<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bop.gov/inmateloc/ |title=Federal Bureau of Prisons Inmate Locator |author=<!--Not stated--> |date= |website=Federal Bureau of Prisons |publisher=United States Department of Justice |access-date=2018-01-14 |quote=Register Number: 18870-111 |archive-date=2020-01-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200126031401/http://www.bop.gov/iloc2/InmateFinderServlet?Transaction=NameSearch&needingMoreList=false&FirstName=Robert&Middle=&LastName=Collins&Race=B&Sex=M&Age=82&x=69&y=21 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

==早年經歷==
烏布利希早年住在奧斯汀市區。幼時是一名[[童軍_(童軍年齡階段)|童軍]]<ref>"[http://money.cnn.com/2015/05/28/technology/silk-road-ross-ulbricht-sentencing/index.html Silk Road's Ross Ulbricht: Drug 'kingpin' or 'idealistic' Boy Scout?] {{Wayback|url=http://money.cnn.com/2015/05/28/technology/silk-road-ross-ulbricht-sentencing/index.html |date=20201205031009 }}" ''[[CNN|CNN]]''/''Money''. 2015-05-28. Retrieved on 2015-06-15.</ref>，並成功獲頒[[鷹級童軍|鷹級童軍]]<ref name=SegalIdealist>Segal, David. "[https://www.nytimes.com/2014/01/19/business/eagle-scout-idealist-drug-trafficker.html?_r=0 Eagle Scout. Idealist. Drug Trafficker?] {{Wayback|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/01/19/business/eagle-scout-idealist-drug-trafficker.html?_r=0 |date=20210414131210 }}" ''The New York Times''. 2014-01-18. Retrieved on  2015-06-10.</ref>。他先後就讀位於奧斯汀附近的西部山脊中学（West Ridge Middle School）和西湖高中（Westlake High School）<ref name=Wired1>{{cite magazine|title = The Untold Story of Silk Road, Part 1|url = https://www.wired.com/2015/04/silk-road-1/|accessdate = 2015-06-09|magazine = Wired|date = 2015|archive-date = 2017-12-01|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20171201214031/https://www.wired.com/2015/04/silk-road-1/|dead-url = no}}</ref>，2002年從高中畢業<ref name=Austinties>"[https://www.statesman.com/news/news/local/man-with-austin-ties-charged-with-running-vast-und/nbDm4/ Man with Austin ties charged with running vast underground drugs website]" (). ''Austin American-Statesman''.2013-10-02. Retrieved on 2015-06-14.</ref>。

他之後憑著全额奖学金就讀[[德克薩斯州大學達拉斯分校|德克薩斯州大學達拉斯分校]]<ref name=SegalIdealist/>，於當中修讀物理，最後於2006年成功取得學士學位<ref name=Austinties/>。接下來他開始在[[宾夕法尼亚州立大学|宾夕法尼亚州立大学]]修讀材料科學與工程硕士課程，並研究[[晶体学|晶体学]]。在烏布利希成功取得硕士學位之前，他就已對[[自由意志主義|自由意志主義]]的經濟理論產生強烈興趣。比方說，他會<nowiki>支持</nowiki>[[路德維希·馮·米塞斯|路德維希·馮·米塞斯]]和[[榮·保羅|榮·保羅]]的主張，並在校园參與有關經濟意識形態的辯論<ref name=Wired1/><ref name=DeweyWaPoProf>Dewey, Caitlin. "[https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/the-switch/wp/2013/10/03/everything-we-know-about-ross-ulbricht-the-outdoorsy-libertarian-behind-silk-road/ Everything we know about Ross Ulbricht, the outdoorsy libertarian behind Silk Road] {{Wayback|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/the-switch/wp/2013/10/03/everything-we-know-about-ross-ulbricht-the-outdoorsy-libertarian-behind-silk-road/ |date=20150513003703 }}". ''Washington Post''. 2013-10-03. Retrieved on 2015-06-15.</ref>。

烏布利希於2009年成功取得硕士學位，並決定回到奧斯汀居住。此時他發現正規工作跟自身的個性不合，故打算自行創業。不過他的第一門事業以失敗告終。他曾試過以-{zh-tw:[[當日沖銷|當日沖銷]];zh-hant:[[當日沖銷|當日沖銷]];zh-hk:[[即日買賣|即日買賣]];zh-cn:[[日內交易|日內交易]];zh-hans:[[日內交易|日內交易]]}-的方式賺錢，亦曾開過一間電子遊戲公司。烏布利希的母親稱，他的[[LinkedIn|LinkedIn]]檔案並沒有提及暗網市場，反而更讓人認為他在營運著一款[[大型多人在线角色扮演游戏|大型多人在线角色扮演游戏]]，上面寫道：「我正在製作一款经济模拟器，它能让人们亲身体验一下活在沒有系統性武力的世界是怎樣的」{{r|mother|page1=7:20}}。

==絲路、被捕與審判==
{{main|絲路 (購物網站)#丝绸之路1.0}}
絲路運行在[[Tor|Tor]]之上，並以[[比特幣|比特幣]]作為交易媒介。Tor是一個運用[[加密協定|加密協定]]的暗网網絡，它使得網絡流量在到達目的地前经由全球志願者免費提供的伺服器路由，以達至隱藏用戶真實IP地址的目的。故此烏布利希能透過把自身的網站以Tor站點的方式營運，來隱藏自身的IP地址<ref name="ars sunk">{{cite web|last1=Mullin|first1=Joe|title=Sunk: How Ross Ulbricht ended up in prison for life|url=https://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/2015/05/sunk-how-ross-ulbricht-ended-up-in-prison-for-life/1/|website=Ars Technica|publisher=Condé Nast|accessdate=2015-11-14|date=2015-05-29|archive-date=2015-06-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150601235653/https://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/2015/05/sunk-how-ross-ulbricht-ended-up-in-prison-for-life/1/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="USA Today shutdown info">{{cite news|last1=Leger|first1=Donna Leinwand|title=How FBI brought down cyber-underworld site Silk Road|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2013/10/21/fbi-cracks-silk-road/2984921/|accessdate=2015-12-13|newspaper=USA Today|date=2014-05-15|archive-date=2015-12-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151212030114/http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2013/10/21/fbi-cracks-silk-road/2984921/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。[[比特幣|比特幣]]則是一款[[加密貨幣|加密貨幣]]；虽然所有的比特币交易都會以[[區塊鏈|區塊鏈]]的形式記錄下來，但由於它不會把用戶身份跟其線上錢包聯繫到一起，故同樣能夠在一定程度上確保匿名性<ref name="Salon Popper excerpt">{{cite news|last1=Popper|first1=Nathaniel|title="We are up to something big": Silk Road discovers Bitcoin|url=http://www.salon.com/2015/05/24/we_are_up_to_something_big_silk_road_discovers_bitcoin/|work=Salon|accessdate=2015-12-13|date=2015-05-24|archive-date=2015-12-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222120801/http://www.salon.com/2015/05/24/we_are_up_to_something_big_silk_road_discovers_bitcoin/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="cnn bitfalls">{{cite web|last1=Pagliery|first1=Jose|title=Bitcoin fallacy led to Silk Road founder's conviction|url=http://money.cnn.com/2015/02/05/technology/security/bitcoin-silk-road/|website=cnn.com|publisher=CNN Money|accessdate=2015-12-13|date=2015-02-05|archive-date=2021-04-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210417093032/https://money.cnn.com/2015/02/05/technology/security/bitcoin-silk-road/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

烏布利希在絲路上的網名為恐怖海盜羅伯茲（Dread Pirate Roberts）。不過他是否此帳戶的唯一使用者這道問題便有一定爭議<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.wired.com/2015/02/ross-ulbricht-didnt-create-silk-roads-dread-pirate-roberts-guy/|title=Ross Ulbricht Didn't Create Silk Road's Dread Pirate Roberts. This Guy Did|last=Greenburg|first=Andy|date=2015-02-09|work=Wired|access-date=2018-05-05|archive-date=2018-06-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180617045930/https://www.wired.com/2015/02/ross-ulbricht-didnt-create-silk-roads-dread-pirate-roberts-guy/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://motherboard.vice.com/en_us/article/qkjm4m/someone-accessed-dread-pirate-roberts-silk-road-operators-account-while-ross-ulbricht-was-in-jail|title=Someone Accessed Silk Road Operator's Account While Ross Ulbricht Was in Jail|last=Koebler|first=Jason|date=2016-12-01|work=Motherboard|access-date=2018-05-05|archive-date=2018-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180308131756/https://motherboard.vice.com/en_us/article/qkjm4m/someone-accessed-dread-pirate-roberts-silk-road-operators-account-while-ross-ulbricht-was-in-jail|dead-url=no}}</ref>。恐怖海盜羅伯茲表示，此一網站的靈感源自「《Alongside Night》和{{link-en|塞繆爾·愛德華·康金三世|Samuel Edward Konkin III}}的作品」<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/andygreenberg/2013/04/29/collected-quotations-of-the-dread-pirate-roberts-founder-of-the-drug-site-silk-road-and-radical-libertarian/|title=Collected Quotations Of The Dread Pirate Roberts, Founder Of Underground Drug Site Silk Road And Radical Libertarian|last=Greenburg|first=Andy|date=2013-04-29|work=Forbes|access-date=2018-05-05|archive-date=2018-06-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612144311/https://www.forbes.com/sites/andygreenberg/2013/04/29/collected-quotations-of-the-dread-pirate-roberts-founder-of-the-drug-site-silk-road-and-radical-libertarian/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

自2010年起，烏布利希便開始著手於建立他的線上市场，視之為線上二手書店的副業。在營運過程中，他還不時在網上發表自身所寫的日記；他在第一篇日記中稍微寫了一些過往經歷，并预测他能透過這次創業，使2011年成為「好景之年」<ref name=Wired1/><ref name="Ars diary">{{cite web|last1=Mullin|first1=Joe|title="I have secrets": Ross Ulbricht's private journal shows Silk Road's birth|url=https://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/2015/01/silk-road-trial-fbi-reveals-whats-on-ross-ulbrichts-computer-in-open-court/|website=Ars Technica|accessdate=2016-03-04|date=2015-01-21|archive-date=2015-01-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150122225354/https://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/2015/01/silk-road-trial-fbi-reveals-whats-on-ross-ulbrichts-computer-in-open-court/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。烏布利希在其LinkedIn頁面上可能稍微暗示過自身跟絲路的關係，他於上面提到了自身的願景：「以经济理论来消弭人与人之间的胁迫和侵略」，並指：「我正在製作一款經濟模擬器，它能讓人們親身體驗一下活在沒有系統性武力的世界是怎樣的」<ref name=DeweyWaPoProf/>。他之後移居至舊金山<ref name=DeweyWaPoProf/>。

[[File:Silk_Road_Seized.jpg|thumb]]查封絲路後，它的首頁就被替換成上述圖像]]
2013年，[[美国国家税务局|美国国家税务局]]的调查人员加里·阿尔福德（Gary Alford）在跟[[美国缉毒局|美国缉毒局]]一起調查絲路時，首次把網名恐怖海盜羅伯茲跟烏布利希劃上聯繫<ref name="Popper">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/12/27/business/dealbook/the-unsung-tax-agent-who-put-a-face-on-the-silk-road.html|title=The Tax Sleuth Who Took Down a Drug Lord|work=New York Times|first=Nathaniel|last=Popper|date=2015-12-25|accessdate=2015-12-26|archive-date=2015-12-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151225215838/https://www.nytimes.com/2015/12/27/business/dealbook/the-unsung-tax-agent-who-put-a-face-on-the-silk-road.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Silk Road: Google search unmasked Dread Pirate Roberts|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/av/magazine-40977474/silk-road-google-search-unmasked-dread-pirate-roberts|accessdate=2017-08-19|work=BBC News|date=2017-08-19|archive-date=2017-08-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170819002514/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/av/magazine-40977474/silk-road-google-search-unmasked-dread-pirate-roberts|dead-url=no}}</ref>。他首先發現絲路早期用於發佈通知的用戶為奧托伊德（altoid），然後在另一論壇上找到由同一名稱的用戶發出的帖文。於是他遵從此一線索，透過程式找出他的電郵地址。電郵地址上包含了他的全名<ref name="Popper"/>。2013年10月，美國聯邦調查局在[[旧金山公立图书馆|旧金山公立图书馆]]格伦公园（Glen Park）分館正式拘捕烏布利希，并指控他為網站的「幕後主腦」<ref name="BBC">{{cite web | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/technology-24842410 | title=Dark net marketplace Silk Road 'back online' | work=BBC | date=2013-11-06 | accessdate=2013-12-20 | archive-date=2013-11-07 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131107014649/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/technology-24842410 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Forbes2">{{cite web | url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/ryanmac/2013/10/02/who-is-ross-ulbricht-piecing-together-the-life-of-the-alleged-libertarian-mastermind-behind-silk-road/2/ | title=Who Is Ross Ulbricht? Piecing Together The Life Of The Alleged Libertarian Mastermind Behind Silk Road [Page 2] | work=Forbes | date=2013-10-02 | accessdate=2013-12-19 | author=Mac, Ryan | archive-date=2013-10-05 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131005023107/https://www.forbes.com/sites/ryanmac/2013/10/02/who-is-ross-ulbricht-piecing-together-the-life-of-the-alleged-libertarian-mastermind-behind-silk-road/2/ | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Guardian">{{cite web|url = https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2013/nov/21/silk-road-founder-held-without-bail|title = Silk Road founder Ross William Ulbricht denied bail|work = The Guardian|date = 2013-11-21|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160305020239/http://www.theguardian.com/technology/2013/nov/21/silk-road-founder-held-without-bail|archivedate = 2016-03-05|access-date = 2020-08-04|dead-url = no}}</ref>。

為了使烏布利希不能夠把[[手提電腦|手提電腦]]內的有關檔案刪除或加密，兩個探員先假裝成情侶，然後在他身旁大吵大鬧，使之分神<ref name="Business Insider arrest story">{{cite news|last=Bertrand|first=Natasha|title=The FBI staged a lovers' fight to catch the kingpin of the web's biggest illegal drug marketplace|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/ross-ulbricht-will-be-sentenced-soon--heres-how-he-was-arrested-2015-5|newspaper=Business Insider|date=2015-05-29|accessdate=2016-05-30|archive-date=2016-06-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160625023157/http://www.businessinsider.com/ross-ulbricht-will-be-sentenced-soon--heres-how-he-was-arrested-2015-5|dead-url=no}}</ref>。隨後第三個探員上場，一手奪走他的電腦，再把之交給探員托马斯·基尔南（Thomas Kiernan）<ref>{{cite web|last1=|first=|title=Trial Transcript, Day 2, page 856|url=https://freeross.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Day_5-2015_Jan_21_Trial_780-1030.pdf#page=77|website=|accessdate=2015-01-21|date=2015-01-21|archive-date=2018-08-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180807032544/https://freeross.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Day_5-2015_Jan_21_Trial_780-1030.pdf#page=77|dead-url=no}}</ref>。基尔南把一隻USB设备插進烏布利希的電腦，然後透過軟件复制关键檔案<ref name="Business Insider arrest story"/>。

[[File:2nd_Cir._oral_argument._15-1815_US_v_Ulbricht_-_audio_extracted.ogg|thumb]]
2014年8月21日，烏布利希正式被落案起訴，罪名為洗錢、電腦入侵、串謀販毒<ref>{{cite web|url = https://freeross.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Ross_Ulbricht_superseding_indictment_8-21-2014.pdf|title = Ross Ulbricht Indictment|work = U.S District Court Southern District of New York|date = 2014-02-04|accessdate = 2014-02-04|author = |archive-date = 2018-08-07|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180807033120/https://freeross.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Ross_Ulbricht_superseding_indictment_8-21-2014.pdf|dead-url = no}}</ref>。法庭下令他在等候審訊期間需[[羈押|還押看管]]<ref name="Guardian" />。

烏布利希在經過2015年1月的陪審團審判後，於2015年2月4日被裁定所有罪名成立<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/tech/tech-news/accused-silk-road-operator-ross-ulbricht-convicted-all-counts-n299606|title=Accused Silk Road Operator Ross Ulbricht Convicted on All Counts|publisher=NBC News|date=2015-02-04|access-date=2015-06-21|archive-date=2015-02-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150207065328/http://www.nbcnews.com/tech/tech-news/accused-silk-road-operator-ross-ulbricht-convicted-all-counts-n299606|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2015年5月29日，法院判處烏布利希雙重[[無期徒刑|無期徒刑]]，40年內不得假釋<ref name="guardian-thielman">{{Cite web|url = https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2015/may/29/silk-road-ross-ulbricht-sentenced|title = Silk Road operator Ross Ulbricht sentenced to life in prison|date = 2015-05-29|accessdate = 2015-10-17|website = The Guardian|publisher = |last = Thielman|first = Sam|archive-date = 2015-05-30|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150530053603/https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2015/may/29/silk-road-ross-ulbricht-sentenced|dead-url = no}}</ref><ref>Greenberg, Andy. "[https://www.forbes.com/sites/andygreenberg/2013/11/06/as-ross-ulbricht-appears-in-new-york-court-his-lawyer-says-hes-not-the-fbis-dread-pirate-roberts/ After Ross Ulbricht's First NY Court Appearance, His Lawyer Says He's Not The FBI's Dread Pirate Roberts] {{Wayback|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/andygreenberg/2013/11/06/as-ross-ulbricht-appears-in-new-york-court-his-lawyer-says-hes-not-the-fbis-dread-pirate-roberts/ |date=20210428140253 }}". ''Forbes''.2013-11-07. Retrieved on 2015-06-15. "Dratel said Ulbricht is now being held at the Metropolitan Detention Center in Brooklyn[...]"</ref>。

联邦检察官還稱，烏布利希曾僱用殺手去嘗試殺掉至少5個人，涉及金額達73萬美元<ref name="Guardian" />。這樣做的背後動機據稱是為了讓自身營運著絲路的真相不被發現<ref name>Alan Klasfeld, [https://www.courthousenews.com/silk-road-murder-threat-shown-as-case-nears-end/ Silk Road Murder Threat Shown as Case Nears End] {{Wayback|url=https://www.courthousenews.com/silk-road-murder-threat-shown-as-case-nears-end/ |date=20210120082824 }}, Courthouse News Service (2015-01-29): "Silk Road founder Ross Ulbricht is not charged with murder-for-hire in his New York trial, but federal prosecutors have long accused him of hiring a hit-man to kill those who threatened his underground online drug empire. Minutes before the second week of Ulbricht's trial ended on Thursday, a jury saw email records supporting this allegation."</ref><ref name=ColeSandick>Cassye M. Cole & Harry Sandick, [https://www.lexology.com/library/detail.aspx?g=859c567f-bb3b-4f3a-b581-037a4e45e523 A Long Journey Through "Silk Road" Appeal: Second Circuit Affirms Conviction and Life Sentence of Silk Road Mastermind] {{Wayback|url=https://www.lexology.com/library/detail.aspx?g=859c567f-bb3b-4f3a-b581-037a4e45e523 |date=20210201205029 }}, Patterson Belknap Webb & Tyler LLP, ''Lexology'',  2017-06-08): "At trial, the government presented evidence that Ulbricht conspired to engage in multiple murders for hire to protect Silk Road's anonymity. Ulbricht was not charged with these offenses. ... At sentencing, in its Pre-Sentence Investigation Report, the U.S. Probation Office referenced the five commissioned murders, as well as six drug-related deaths connected with Silk Road. On May 29, 2015, the district court sentenced Ulbricht to life in prison, pursuant to the Guidelines advisory sentence range, and based on the recommendation of the U.S. Probation Office. ... While the Court recognized that a life sentence for selling drugs was rare and could be considered harsh, the facts of this case involved much more than routine drug dealings—namely that Ulbricht commissioned at least five murders for hire and did not challenge those murders on appeal."</ref>。检察官认为，當中沒有一單是真的成事的<ref name="Guardian" />。儘管在纽约联邦法院的审判當中，它並沒有控以烏布利希相關罪名<ref name="Guardian" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailydot.com/crime/silk-road-murder-charges-ross-ulbricht/|website=[[The_Daily_Dot|The Daily Dot]]|title=The mystery of the disappearing Silk Road murder charges|author=Patrick Howell O'Neill|date=2014-10-22|access-date=2020-08-04|archive-date=2014-10-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141023152833/http://www.dailydot.com/crime/silk-road-murder-charges-ross-ulbricht/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，但呈堂證據支持上述指控<ref name="Guardian" /><ref name=ColeSandick/>。 法官在判处烏布利希無期徒刑時，考慮到了有關他僱用殺手的證據。第二巡迴上訴法院在決定維持原判時亦考慮了有關因素<ref name=ColeSandick/>。[[美国马里兰联邦地区法院|美国马里兰联邦地区法院]]曾對烏布利希提出單獨起訴，指控他僱兇殺害他的一名僱員。不過在2018年7月，最高法院決定再度維持原判後，有關起訴被檢察官無條件駁回<ref>Joseph Cox, [https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/nz7bmb/murdered-silk-road-employee-sentenced-to-time-served 'Murdered' Silk Road Employee Sentenced to Time Served] {{Wayback|url=https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/nz7bmb/murdered-silk-road-employee-sentenced-to-time-served |date=20200920055954 }}, Vice (2016-01-26).</ref><ref name="Doherty">{{cite web |url=https://reason.com/2018/07/25/ross-ulbrichts-murder-for-hire-charges-d/ |title=Ross Ulbricht's Murder-for-Hire Charges Dropped by U.S. Attorney |first=Brian |last=Doherty |date=2018-07-25 |website=Reason.com |access-date= |quote= |archive-date=2019-04-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190427084729/https://reason.com/2018/07/25/ross-ulbrichts-murder-for-hire-charges-d/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://freeross.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Doc_14_Dismissal_Indictment_7-26-2018.pdf/ |title=Motion to Dismiss Indictment and Superseding Indictment |author=United States District Court for the District of Maryland |date= |website= |publisher= |access-date= |quote= |archive-date=2018-08-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180807033225/https://freeross.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Doc_14_Dismissal_Indictment_7-26-2018.pdf/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

==定罪后==
烏布利希于2016年1月向美国第二巡回上诉法院提出上诉。上訴方主要認為檢方非法隱瞞了美國緝毒局探員在調查絲路時，參與[[瀆職|瀆職]]行為的證據。之後兩名探員因此而被定罪<ref name="appeal-wired">{{cite web|url=https://www.wired.com/2016/01/ross-ulbrichts-defense-focuses-on-corrupt-feds-in-silk-road-appeal/|title=In Silk Road Appeal, Ross Ulbricht's Defense Focuses on Corrupt Feds|first=Andy|last=Greenberg|work=Wired|date=2016-01-12|accessdate=2016-01-13|archive-date=2016-01-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160113044804/https://www.wired.com/2016/01/ross-ulbrichts-defense-focuses-on-corrupt-feds-in-silk-road-appeal/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。烏布利希还认为他的判刑過重<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-cyber-silkroad-idUSKBN18R23A|title=Silk Road website founder loses appeal of conviction, life sentence|last=Stempel|first=Jonathan|date=2017-05-31|work=Reuters|access-date=2018-05-05|archive-date=2018-06-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180615005004/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-cyber-silkroad-idUSKBN18R23A|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-cyber-silkroad-idUSKBN18R23A |title=存档副本 |access-date=2020-08-04 |archive-date=2018-06-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180615005004/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-cyber-silkroad-idUSKBN18R23A |dead-url=no }}</ref>。口頭辯論於2016年10月進行<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wired.com/2016/10/judges-question-ulbrichts-life-sentence-silk-road-appeal/|title=Judges Question Ross Ulbricht's Life Sentence in Silk Road Appeal|first=Andy|last=Greenberg|date=2016-10-06|accessdate=2016-10-15|work=Wired|archive-date=2016-10-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161007085909/https://www.wired.com/2016/10/judges-question-ulbrichts-life-sentence-silk-road-appeal/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=ColeSandick/><ref name=2dCirOpinion>''[http://scholar.google.com/scholar_case?case=7379835016583659897 United States v. Ulbricht] {{Wayback|url=http://scholar.google.com/scholar_case?case=7379835016583659897 |date=20210824033000 }}'', 858 F.3d 71 (2d. Cir. 2017)</ref>。2017年5月，第二巡回法院判處烏布利希上訴失敗，法官杰拉德·林奇（Gerard E. Lynch）為此擇寫了一份意見書<ref name=ColeSandick/>，長達139頁<ref name=ColeSandick/>。當中法院判斷地區法院否決「烏布利希排除某些非法證據的申請」的決定是正確的；接納了地區法院的專家證供和發現；驳回了烏布利希有關判決過重的論點<ref name=ColeSandick/><ref name=2dCirOpinion/>。

2017年12月，烏布利希向美国最高法院提出呈请，要求法院就证据和量刑问题审理他的上诉<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news.vice.com/en_us/article/kzn7a9/the-supreme-court-is-silk-road-founder-ross-ulbrichts-last-hope|title=The Supreme Court is Silk Road founder Ross Ulbricht's last hope|work=VICE News|access-date=2018-02-24|language=en|archive-date=2018-02-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180203042553/https://news.vice.com/en_us/article/kzn7a9/the-supreme-court-is-silk-road-founder-ross-ulbrichts-last-hope|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.supremecourt.gov/DocketPDF/17/17-950/24860/20171222095855755_Ulbricht%20cert%20petition.pdf|title=Ulbricht v. U.S.|last=Ulbricht|first=Ross|date=2017-12-22|website=SupremeCourt.Gov|access-date=2018-02-23|archive-date=2018-02-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180220151956/https://www.supremecourt.gov/DocketPDF/17/17-950/24860/20171222095855755_Ulbricht%20cert%20petition.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。21個[[法院之友|法院之友]]向法院提出了5份意見書，以支持烏布利希的呈请，其中包括{{link-en|全國律師協會|National Lawyers Guild}}、美国黑十字会（American Black Cross）、{{link-en|理性基金會|Reason Foundation}}、{{link-en|药物政策联盟|Drug Policy Alliance}}、缩小DC基金会（Downsize DC Foundation）<ref name=":0" />。美国政府提交了反对烏布利希呈请的回應書<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=http://www.scotusblog.com/case-files/cases/ulbricht-v-united-states/|title=Ulbricht v. United States|work=SCOTUSblog|access-date=2018-02-24|language=en-US|archive-date=2018-02-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180227161804/http://www.scotusblog.com/case-files/cases/ulbricht-v-united-states/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.supremecourt.gov/DocketPDF/17/17-950/38031/20180307141700560_17-950%20Ulbricht%20FINAL.pdf|title=Ulbricht v. U.S.|last=Francisco|first=Noel|date=2018-03-07|website=SupremeCourt.Gov|access-date=2018-03-31|archive-date=2018-04-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180401075233/https://www.supremecourt.gov/DocketPDF/17/17-950/38031/20180307141700560_17-950%20Ulbricht%20FINAL.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2018年6月28日，最高法院驳回了烏布利希的呈请<ref name="Reuters">{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-court-silkroad/us-supreme-court-turns-away-silk-road-website-founders-appeal-idUSKBN1JO1YX|title=U.S. Supreme Court turns away Silk Road website founder's appeal|work=Reuters|date=2018-06-28|language=en-US|accessdate=2020-08-04|archive-date=2020-11-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109041240/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-court-silkroad/us-supreme-court-turns-away-silk-road-website-founders-appeal-idUSKBN1JO1YX|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2019年，烏布利希的辩护律师以无效辩护（ineffective assistance of counsel）為由，嘗試去撤-{}-銷無期徒刑此一處罰；2019年8月，申請被驳回<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://nypost.com/2019/08/12/silk-road-mastermind-ross-ulbricht-attempts-to-vacate-life-sentence/ |title=Silk Road mastermind Ross Ulbricht attempts to vacate life sentence |access-date=2020-08-04 |archive-date=2019-08-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190813000636/https://nypost.com/2019/08/12/silk-road-mastermind-ross-ulbricht-attempts-to-vacate-life-sentence/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

